{"title_page": "Polydistortion", "text_new": "{{refimprove|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Polydistortion\n| type       = [[Album]]\n| artist     = [[GusGus]]\n| cover      = Polydistortion.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = 7 April 1997\n| recorded   = 1995\u20131997\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = {{hlist|[[Electronica]]|[[techno]]}}\n| length     = 61:02\n| label      = [[4AD]]\n| producer   = {{hlist|GusGus|P\u00e1ll Borg}}\n| prev_title = GusGus\n| prev_year  = 1995\n| next_title = [[This Is Normal]]\n| next_year  = 1999\n| misc       = {{Singles\n | name        = Polydistortion\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Polyesterday\n | single1date = 7 October 1996\n | single2     = Believe\n | single2date = 10 February 1997\n | single3     = Polyesterday\n | single3date = 9 February 1998 (reissue)\n}}\n}}\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|4.5|5}}<ref name=\"AMG\">{{cite web |first=Ned |last=Raggett |title=Polydistortion \u2013 GusGus |url=https://www.allmusic.com/album/polydistortion-mw0000019020 |publisher=[[AllMusic]] |accessdate=1 January 2016}}</ref>\n| rev2 = ''[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]]''\n| rev2Score = 8.3/10<ref name=\"PM\">{{cite web |first=Ryan |last=Schreiber |title=GusGus: Polydistortion |url=http://pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/18248/Gusgus_Polydistortion |work=[[Pitchfork (website)|Pitchfork]] |accessdate=1 January 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090227024716/http://pitchforkmedia.com/article/record_review/18248/Gusgus_Polydistortion |archivedate=27 February 2009}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Q (magazine)|Q]]''\n| rev3Score = {{Rating|4|5}}<ref>{{cite journal |title=GusGus: Polydistortion |work=[[Q (magazine)|Q]] |issue=128 |date=May 1997 |page=122}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Polydistortion''''' is the second [[studio album]] by Icelandic [[electronic music]] band [[GusGus]]. The album was released on 7 April 1997 on [[4AD]], serving as their first release on the label.\n\nThe songs \"Why?\" and the band's cover of [[Slowblow]]'s \"Is Jesus Your Pal?\" feature [[Emil\u00edana Torrini]] on vocals.<ref name=\"Discogs\">{{cite web |title=GusGus - Polydistortion (CD, Album) at Discogs |url=http://www.discogs.com/Gus-Gus-Polydistortion/release/329559 |accessdate=1 January 2016}}</ref> Most of the material on the album had previously been released independently, as the album ''GusGus'' in 1995.\n\nAs of March 1999, the album has sold 40,000 copies in United States and worldwide sales stand at over 150,000 copies.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.hr/books?id=nw4EAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA32&dq=gus+gus+album+sales&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjU4IKD3OjVAhWEORoKHf2hCbIQ6AEIMjAD#v=onepage&q=gus%20gus%20album%20sales&f=false|publisher=Billboard|title=Iceland's GusGus Highlights Its Pop Side With 4AD/WB\u2019s \u201cNormal\u201d \n|first=Mark|last=Solomons|page=32|date=20 March 1999|accessdate=15 April 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{tracklist\n| collapsed       = \n| headline        = \n| title1          = Oh\n| note1         = Edit\n| writer1         = {{hlist|Dan\u00edel \u00c1ug\u00fast|Herb Legowitz|[[Arthur Lyman]]}}\n| length1         = 1:17\n| title2          = Gun\n| writer2         = \u00c1ug\u00fast\n| length2         = 6:08\n| title3          = Believe\n| writer3         = {{hlist|\u00c1ug\u00fast|P\u00e1ll Gardarsson|Siggi Kjartansson|[[Robert \"Kool\" Bell]]|[[Ronald Bell (musician)|Ronald Bell]]|Donald Boyce|Robert \"Spike\" Mickens|[[Claydes Charles Smith]]|Dennis Thomas|Rick Westfield}}\n| length3         = 7:18\n| title4          = Polyesterday\n| writer4         = \u00c1ug\u00fast\n| length4         = 4:52\n| title5          = Barry\n| writer5         = {{hlist|\u00c1ug\u00fast|Magn\u00fas Jonsson}}\n| length5         = 5:58\n| title6          = Cold Breath '79\n| writer6         = {{hlist|Gardarsson|Kjartansson}}\n| length6         = 6:43\n| title7          = Why?\n| writer7         = Jonsson\n| length7  