ces==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:1997 albums]]\n[[Category:GusGus albums]]\n[[Category:4AD albums]]\n", "name_user": "Holiday56", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Polydistortion"}
{"title_page": "David James (footballer, born 1917)", "text_new": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = David James\n|image       = \n|image_size  =\n|caption     = \n|fullname    = \n|birth_date  = 19 September 1917<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n|birth_place = [[Swansea]], Wales<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n| death_date = {{death date and age|1981|12|12|1917|09|19|df=y}}<ref name=\"hugman\">{{Hugman|10037|accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n| death_place = [[Swansea]], Wales<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n|height      = \n|position    = [[Forward (association football)|Centre forward]]\n|youthyears1 =\n|youthclubs1 =\n|years1      = ?\u20131934\n|clubs1      = Midland Athletic<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n|caps1       = \n|goals1      =\n|years2      = 1934\u20131935\n|clubs2      = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n|caps2       = \n|goals2      =\n|years3      = 1935\u20131937\n|clubs3      = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n|caps3       = 5\n|goals3      = 0\n|years4      = 1937\u20131938\n|clubs4      = [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]\n|caps4       = 43\n|goals4      = 42\n|years5      = 1938\u2013????\n|clubs5      = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|caps5       = 0\n|goals5      = 0\n|years6      = 1947\u20131948\n|clubs6      = [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea Town]]\n|caps6       = 12\n|goals6      = 7\n|years7      = 1948\u2013????\n|clubs7      = [[Haverfordwest County A.F.C.|Haverfordwest County]]\n|caps7       = \n|goals7      =\n|totalcaps   = \n|totalgoals  = \n}}\n'''David James''' (9 September 1917 \u2013 12 December 1981) was a Welsh professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|centre forward]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Swansea]], James signed for [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] in May 1935 from [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]. During his time with Bradford City he made five appearances in the Football League.<ref>Frost, p. 384</ref> He left the club in July 1937 to play for [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]].<ref>Frost, p. 400</ref> He transferred to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] for \u00a3200 in April 1938.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/PlayersAZ/AZJ.htm|title=Complete A-Z of Mossley Players|work=Mossley Web|accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe joined [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea Town]] in May 1947, helping them win the 1947 London Combination Cup final.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" /> He scored on his Football League debut for the club at Bristol City four months later.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" /> He netted seven goals in 12 League games before joining [[Haverfordwest County A.F.C.|Haverfordwest County]] in August 1948 where he became captain, then manager.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" />\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|last=Frost|first=Terry|title=Bradford City A Complete Record 1903-1988|publisher=Breedon Books Sport|year=1988|isbn=0-907969-38-0}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:James, David}}\n[[Category:1917 births]]\n[[Category:Welsh footballers]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mossley A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:1981 deaths]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Swansea City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Haverfordwest County A.F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:Haverfordwest County A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Welsh football managers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Swansea]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-1910s-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n|name        = David James\n|image       = \n|image_size  =\n|caption     = \n|fullname    = \n|birth_date  = 19 September 1917<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n|birth_place = [[Swansea]], Wales<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n\n| death_date = {{death date and age|1981|12|12|1917|09|19|df=y}}<ref name=\"hugman\">{{cite web |url=http://hugmansfootballers.com/player/10037 |title=Dai James |website=Hugman's Footballers |accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n| death_place = [[Swansea]], Wales<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n\n|height      = \n|position    = [[Forward (association football)|Centre forward]]\n|youthyears1 =\n|youthclubs1 = \n\n|years1      = ? \u2013 1934\n|clubs1      = Midland Athletic<ref name=\"hugman\" />\n|caps1       = \n|goals1      = \n\n\n|years2      = 1934\u20131935\n|clubs2      = [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]\n|caps2       = \n|goals2      = \n\n|years3      = 1935\u20131937\n|clubs3      = [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]]\n|caps3       = 5\n|goals3      = 0\n\n|years4      = 1937\u20131938\n|clubs4      = [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]]\n|caps4       = 43\n|goals4      = 42\n\n|years5      = 1938\u2013\n|clubs5      = [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]]\n|caps5       = 0\n|goals5      = 0\n\n|years6      = 1947\u20131948\n|clubs6      = [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea Town]]\n|caps6       = 12\n|goals6      = 7\n\n|years7      = 1948\u2013\n|clubs7      = [[Haverfordwest County A.F.C.|Haverfordwest County]]\n|caps7       = \n|goals7      = \n\n|totalcaps   = \n|totalgoals  = \n}}\n'''David 'Dai'<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" /> James''' (9 September 1917 \u2013 12 December 1981) was a Welsh professional [[association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|centre forward]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Swansea]], James signed for [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] in May 1935 from [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]]. During his time with Bradford City he made five appearances in the Football League.<ref>Frost, p. 384</ref> He left the club in July 1937 to play for [[Mossley A.F.C.|Mossley]].<ref>Frost, p. 400</ref> He transferred to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] for \u00a3200 in April 1938.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mossleyweb.com/PlayersAZ/AZJ.htm|title=Complete A-Z of Mossley Players|work=Mossley Web|accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe joined [[Swansea City A.F.C.|Swansea Town]] in May 1947, helping them win the 1947 London Combination Cup final.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" /> He scored on his Football League debut for the club at Bristol City four months later.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" /> He netted seven goals in 12 League games before joining [[Haverfordwest County A.F.C.|Haverfordwest County]] in August 1948 where he became captain, then manager.<ref name=\"mossleyweb.com\" />\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|last=Frost|first=Terry|title=Bradford City A Complete Record 1903-1988|publisher=Breedon Books Sport|year=1988|isbn=0-907969-38-0}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:James, David}}\n[[Category:1917 births]]\n[[Category:Welsh footballers]]\n[[Category:Leeds United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Bradford City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Mossley A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:1981 deaths]]\n[[Category:Chelsea F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Swansea City A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Haverfordwest County A.F.C. managers]]\n[[Category:Haverfordwest County A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Welsh football managers]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Swansea]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-1910s-stub}}\n", "name_user": "GiantSnowman", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_James_(footballer,_born_1917)"}
