s basketball seasons]]\n[[Category:2020\u201321 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|UCF]]\n[[Category:2020 in sports in Florida|UCF Knights men's basketball]]\n[[Category:2021 in sports in Florida|UCF Knights men's basketball]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|University of Central Florida NCAA team}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| sport=Basketball\n| year = 2020\u201321\n| prev_year = 2019\u201320\n| next_year = 2021\u201322\n| team =  UCF Knights\n| logo = UCF Knights logo.svg\n| logo_size = 100px\n| conference = American Athletic Conference\n| short_conf = AAC\n| CoachRank = \n| APRank = \n| record =\n| conf_record = \n| head_coach = [[Johnny Dawkins]]\n| hc_year = 5th\n| asst_coach1 = Kevin Norris\n| ac1_year = 5th\n| asst_coach2 = [[Vince Taylor (basketball)|Vince Taylor]]\n| ac2_year = 4th\n| asst_coach3 = [[Robbie Laing]]\n| ac3_year = 5th\n| arena = [[Addition Financial Arena]]\n| champion =  \n| tourney = \n| tourney_result = \n}}\n{{2020\u201321 American Athletic Conference men's basketball standings}}\nThe '''2020\u201321 UCF Knights men's basketball team''' represents the [[University of Central Florida]] during the [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The Knights are members of the [[American Athletic Conference]]. The Knights, in the program's 52nd season of basketball, are led by fifth-year head coach [[Johnny Dawkins]] and play their home games at the [[Addition Financial Arena]] on the university's main campus in [[Orlando, Florida|Orlando]], [[Florida]].\n\n==Previous season==\nThe [[2019\u201320 UCF Knights men's basketball team|Knights]] finished the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2019\u201320 season]] 16\u201314 overall and 7\u201311 in [[2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|AAC play]] to finish in eighth place. They entered as the No. 8 seed in the [[2020 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|AAC Tournament]], which was ultimately cancelled due to the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]].\n\n==Offseason==\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Number !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for departure\n|-\n| Yuat Alok || 0 || F || 6'11\" || 225 || {{sort|3|Junior}} || [[Auckland|Auckland, New Zealand]] || Transferred to [[Southern Utah Thunderbirds men's basketball|Southern Utah]] (mid-season)<ref>{{cite web |last1= Lester|first1=Bryson|title=Thunderbirds Add Top-Tier Transfer Yuat Alok|url=https://suutbirds.com/news/2020/1/13/mens-basketball-thunderbirds-add-top-tier-transfer-yuat-alok.aspx|website=suutbirds.com  |accessdate=8 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| Matt Milon || 2 || G || 6'5\" || 210 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Oviedo, Florida|Oviedo, FL]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Ceasar DeJesus || 4 || G || 6'2\" || 190 || {{sort|3.5|RS Junior}} || [[Jersey City, New Jersey|Jersey City, NJ]] || Play professionally<ref>{{cite web |last1=Murphy |first1=Brian |title=Ceasar DeJesus Leaving UCF, Planning to Go Pro |url=https://www.blackandgoldbanneret.com/basketball/2020/3/18/21185683/ceasar-dejesus-leaving-ucf-planning-to-go-pro |date=18 Mar 2020 |website=blackandgoldbanneret.com |publisher=[[SB Nation]] |accessdate=16 Apr 2020 }}</ref>\n|-\n| Dazon Ingram || 12 || G || 6'6\" || 205 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Theodore, Alabama|Theodore, AL]] || Graduated\n|-\n| Frank Bertz || 20 || G || 6'5\" || 180 || {{sort|4|Senior}} || [[Hesperia, California|Hesperia, CA]] || Graduated\n|}\n\n===Incoming Transfers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n! Name !! Pos. !! Height !! Weight !! Year !! Hometown !! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| Darius Perry || G || {{sort|##|6'2\"}} || 195 || {{sort|5|Graduate Student}} || [[Powder Springs, Georgia|Powder Springs, GA]] || Transferred from [[Louisville Cardinals men's basketball|Louisville]] after graduating. Will have one year of eligibility beginn